<section class="section" aria-labelledby="cookies-title">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="section-title" id="cookies-title">Cookie Consent Terms</h1>
    <p class="lead measure">
      These terms describe how BrazilDecoded uses cookies and similar
      technologies, in line with Brazil's data protection law (LGPD).
    </p>

    <h2>What are cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files stored in your browser that help the site
      remember your preferences and understand how content is used.
    </p>

    <h2>Types of cookies</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Essential:</strong> enable core site functionality.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Performance and analytics:</strong> measure usage and help
        improve navigation.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Marketing:</strong> may be used for campaigns and measurement
        when applicable.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Consent and legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      For non-essential cookies, we request your consent (LGPD art. 7, I).
      Essential cookies may be used to ensure the site works properly and to
      protect operations.
    </p>

    <h2>Consent record and management</h2>
    <p>
      The cookie banner allows you to accept or reject. Your choice is stored
      in your browser. To withdraw consent, you can clear site data in your
      browser or block cookies.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We may use third-party services (for example, Google) for analytics and
      measurement. These providers may set cookies according to their policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Data subject rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may request confirmation, access, correction, portability, deletion,
      and withdrawal of consent, as applicable. To exercise your rights, use
      the contact form.
    </p>

    <h2>Updates</h2>
    <p>
      This policy may be updated to reflect technical or legal changes. We
      recommend reviewing this page periodically.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions, contact us via the form:
      <a href="/pages/contato.html">/pages/contato.html</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
